{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10c57043-cd98-45c0-86d5-15f5ed6d812c","content":"Since you already have the dump file, you're past the collection phase. Here's how to analyze it:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap statistics |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\n**Quick triage flow:**\n1. `pe` — see the exception that caused the crash\n2. `clrthreads` — find the faulting thread\n3. `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — get its stack trace\n\n**Alternatives:** You can also use **lldb** (Linux/macOS) with the SOS plugin, or **WinDbg** (Windows) for deeper native-level analysis.\n\nWould you like help running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9ac818f-64e5-48cb-98d7-7d521e08151a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill doesn't apply here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"2C43:12EFE2:28C973F:2D5F2BC:69F94EDC"},"id":"57cf85c4-0b52-4f7a-9db5-7296fb54a4ce","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:59:03.702Z","parentId":"7de3d5f2-c4c2-4b38-93f6-6613614dc92b"}
